INPROJECT

This program checks to see if the current (or specified) user is in the project
given as a positional argument.

Synopsis:
$ inproject <projectname(s)> [-af <afile>] [-u <username>] [-V]

Arguments:
<projectname(s)>	project name(s) to check
-af <afile>		argument-list file
-u <username>		alternative username to check
-V			print command version to standard-error and then exit

Returns:
0			YES, user is in the given projects
1			NO
X			other (some kind of error)

